            . I am brother of James Reading - he <rs id="t18290115-129-viclabel674" type="occupation">keeps a grocer's shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290115-129-victim1010 t18290115-129-viclabel674"></join>. On the evening of the 16th of December, about half-past nine o'clock, I was having my supper, and was informed some boys were at the door; I ran out, and saw the prisoner with this drum of figs in his hand; he dropped it at the step of the door, and ran away - I pursued, and he was taken at the top of the street; it my brother's property.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I saw some persons run - I ran, and a gentleman stopped me, and said I had stolen a box of figs; the officer told the witness he must swear that he saw me drop them, or else they could not hurt me.</p>
